archive.org/web/20190823004816/https://gulfnews.com/uae/principal-matters---february-17-2003-1.347529|archive-date=2019-08-23|access-date=2019-08-23|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.khaleejtimes.com/nation/education/investiture-ceremony-for-plus-two-students|title=Investiture ceremony for Plus Two students|date=2012-04-21|newspaper=Khaleej Times|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823004255/https://www.khaleejtimes.com/nation/education/investiture-ceremony-for-plus-two-students|archive-date=2019-08-23|access-date=2018-08-23|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n | principal_label1        = Vice Principal\n | principal1              = Shobha Mohan\n | principal_label2        = Vice Principal of Academics\n | principal2              = Sindu Anand\n | principal_label3        = School Supervisor\n | principal3              = Vimi Bhadrakumar\n | head_teacher            = \n | staff                   = \n | faculty                 = 139\n | teaching_staff          = \n | employees               = \n | key_people              = \n | grades                  = [[Kindergarten|K]] through [[Twelfth grade|{{Ordinal|12|sup=yes}}]]\n | gender                  = \n | age_range               = 4 to 18\n | enrollment              = 1700\n | enrollment_as_of        = \n | classes                 = 60+\n | average_class_size      = 30\n | medium_of_language      = English\n | houses                  = {{Unbulleted list|{{Color box|#50C878}} Emerald|{{Color box|#E0115F}} Ruby|{{Color box|#0F52BA}} Sapphire|{{Color box|#FFC87C}} Topaz}}\n | song                    = ''We'll sing the bells of Indian School Ajman''\n | accreditation           = \n | affiliation             = [[Ministry of Education (United Arab Emirates)|Ministry of Education, UAE]]\n | information             = \n | website                 = {{URL|https://gisajman.com}}\n | footnotes               = \n | module                  = <mapframe frameless align=\"center\" width=\"280\" height=\"280\" zoom=\"12\" latitude=\"25.41\" longitude=\"55.48\">[{ \"type\": \"ExternalData\", \"service\": \"geoshape\", \"ids\": \"Q159477\", \"properties\": { \"fill\": \"#E0115F\", \"title\": \"[[Emirate of Ajman]]\", \"description\": \"[[File:Ajman ar.jpg|220px|link=]]\" } }, { \"type\": \"Feature\", \"properties\": { \"title\": \"Indian School Ajman\", \"description\": \"Location of ISA\", \"marker-symbol\": \"school\", \"marker-size\": \"large\", \"marker-color\": \"#50C878\" }, \"geometry\": { \"type\": \"Point\", \"coordinates\": [55.49298, 25.39826] } }]</mapframe><span style=\"font-weight: normal;\">Location of ISA (emerald pin icon) in the Emirate of Ajman, shown in ruby (click to enlarge)</span>\n | picture                 = \n | picture_caption         = \n | picture2                = \n | picture_caption2        = \n}}\n'''Global Indian School Ajman''' (formerly '''Indian School Ajman''') is a private Indian [[K-12]] school in [[Ajman]], [[United Arab Emirates]], established in 1988.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.dubaifaqs.com/indian-school-ajman.php|title=Indian School Ajman|website=Dubai FAQs|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823003544/http://www.dubaifaqs.com/indian-school-ajman.php|archive-date=2019-08-23|access-date=2019-08-11|url-status=dead}}</ref> The school is recognized by the UAE's [[Ministry of Education (United Arab Emirates)|Ministry of Education]] and affiliated with the [[Central Board of Secondary Education|Central Board of Secondary Education]] in [[New Delhi|New Delhi, India]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.thelearningpoint.net/home/school-listings/cbse-32/INDIAN-SCHOOL-P-O-BOX-1827-AJMAN-U-A-E-6630021|title=Indian School Ajman|website=The Learning Point|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823001635/http://www.thelearningpoint.net/home/school-listings/cbse-32/INDIAN-SCHOOL-P-O-BOX-1827-AJMAN-U-A-E-6630021|archive-date=2019-08-23|access-date=2019-08-23|url-status=dead}}</ref> \n\nIndian School Ajman was recognized as one of the best schools in the UAE by EW Global School Rankings, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.educationworld.in/ew-global-school-rankings-2019-20|title=EW Global School Rankings 2019-20|website=Education World|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190920054420/https://www.educationworld.in/ew-global-school-rankings-2019-20|archive-date=2019-09-20|access-date=2019-09-20}}</ref>\n\nThe principal, Malathi Das, was awarded the [[Central Board of Secondary Education|CBSE]]'s Teacher of the Year award in 2002.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://gulfnews.com/uae/against-all-odds-1.401435|title=Against all odds: Malathi Das|last=Nagarkar|first=Jyotsna A.|date=2002-10-21|newspaper=Gulf News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190823005601/https://gulfnews.com/uae/against-all-odds-1.401435|archive-date=2019-08-23|access-date=2019-08-23|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nIndian School Ajman was established in 1988 to serve the Indian expatriate community of Ajman.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indianschoolajman.org/messages-1|title=Message from the Hon. Chairman: T. Mohanachandran|website=Indian School Ajman|access-date=2019-08-11}}</ref> The school presented its first batch of students for the [[All India Senior School Certificate Examination]] in 1992.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indianschoolajman.org|title=Indian School Ajman|website=Indian School Ajman|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811200647/https://www.indianschoolajman.org/|archive-date=2019-08-11|access-date=2019-08-11|url-status=dead}}</ref> Initially, the school was the only one in its neighborhood; it started off with just eight faculty members, as enrollments started small and grew slowly. Presently, it has more than 150 staff members and a total enrollment of about 1700 students.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.edarabia.com/105700/indian-school-ajman-uae/|title=Indian School Ajman|website=Edarabia|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190811205645/https://www.edarabia.com/105700/indian-school-ajman-uae/|archive-date=2019-08-11|access-date=2019-08-11|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n== Campus ==\nThe school was initially opened in a villa.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indianschoolajman.org/principal|title=Message from the Principal: Malathi Das|website=Indian School Ajman|access-date=2019-08-23}}</ref> In 1991, it moved to its new premises, granted by the [[Humaid bin Rashid Al Nuaimi III|ruler of Ajman]], at the heart of [[Ajman]] city. \nThe school again moved to a bigger campus in 2020, following which it was renamed 'Global Indian School Ajman'.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{URL|https://gisajman.com|Official website}}\n* {{URL|https://indianschoolajman.org|Old website}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1988]]\n[[Category:Education in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Indian international schools in the United Arab Emirates]]\n[[Category:Education in Ajman]]\n[[Category:Schools in Ajman]]\n", "text_old": "{{Distinguish|International Indian School Ajman}}\n{{Infobox school\n | name                    = Global Indian School Ajman\n | native_name             = \u0627\u0644\u0645\u062f\u0631\u0633\u0629 \u0627\u0644\u0647\u0646\u062f\u064a\u0629 \u0628\u0639\u062c\u0645\u0627\u0646\n | logo                    = [[File:Indian School Ajman, Official Banner.jpg|250px|center]]\n | logo_size               = \n | logo_alt                = \n | seal_image              = \n | seal_size               = \n | seal_alt                = \n | image                   = [[File:Indian School Ajman, Assembly.png|250px|center]]\n | image_size              = \n | alt                     = \n | caption                 = \n | address                 = Sheikh Maktoum Bin Rashid Street\n | region                  = Al Jurf\n | city                    = [[Ajman]]\n | state                   = [[Emirate of Ajman]]\n | country                 = [[United Arab Emirates]]\n | coordinates             = {{Coord|25.3983|55.4930|typ